    "value": "The Regulation (EU) 2024/2847—commonly known as the EU Cyber Resilience Act (CRA)—was adopted on 23 October 2024 and sets horizontal cybersecurity requirements for products with digital elements. This act is available on EUR-Lex in full text, including its annexes such as \"ANNEX VII\"【3:0†Regulation - 2024/2847 - EN - EUR-Lex†https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/2847/oj/eng】.\n\nWhile direct excerpts of \"ANNEX VII\" are not reproduced in the search results, the linkage is confirmed: Annex VII is part of Regulation (EU) 2024/2847 and can be found in the official publication in EUR-Lex, which hosts all legal texts, including annexes, in HTML and PDF formats【3:0†Regulation - 2024/2847 - EN - EUR-Lex†https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/2847/oj/eng】.\n\nFor the official and authentic content of ANNEX VII—such as its scope, definitions, and requirements—you should refer to the official document here: [EUR-Lex Regulation 2024/2847](https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2024/2847/oj/eng).\n\nAdditional context:\n- The Cyber Resilience Act introduces mandatory security requirements for digital products placed on the EU market, addressing issues like vulnerabilities and security updates.\n- Annexes in such regulations typically detail technical, procedural, or compliance provisions that supplement the main articles of the Regulation.\n\nIf you are looking for a summary or practical tools for compliance (including directions referencing Annex VII), third-party resources and assessment tools based on the official texts are available, but for legal precision and completeness, consult the official EUR-Lex document【3:9†CRA Gap Assessment Tool | EU Cyber Resilience Act 2024/2847 - Etsy†https://www.etsy.com/hk-en/listing/4484179719/cra-gap-assessment-tool-eu-cyber】.\n\nIf you require the exact textual content of ANNEX VII, you must access it through the Regulation (EU) 2024/2847 as published in the Official Journal on EUR-Lex【3:0†source】.",
