{
  "type": "text",
  "text": {
    "value": "\"ANNEX VII\" of Regulation (EU) 2024/2847, also referred to as the Cyber Resilience Act (CRA), sets out the requirements for the content of the technical documentation for products with digital elements that are placed on the EU market.\n\n**Summary of ANNEX VII Content:**\n- **Purpose:** Annex VII aims to specify what information manufacturers must include in their technical documentation to demonstrate conformity with the cybersecurity requirements of the CRA. This documentation is crucial for market surveillance, conformity assessment, and supporting the enforcement of the regulation.\n- **Key Components:** Typically, Annex VII requires the following elements:\n  - A general description of the product, including its intended purpose.\n  - Detailed design and manufacturing information.\n  - Risk analysis and assessment procedures undertaken.\n  - Technical solutions applied to meet essential cybersecurity requirements.\n  - List of harmonized standards or technical specifications used.\n  - Reports of any tests performed.\n  - Documentation on the vulnerability handling processes, including updates and mitigation mechanisms.\n- **Regulatory Context:** Compliance with Annex VII is mandatory for all products with digital elements marketed in the EU. This is integral to demonstrate conformity with the essential cybersecurity requirements (Annex I). Annex VII is part of a broader set of annexes that detail requirements for declarations of conformity, important or critical product classes, and assessment procedures【3:2†Cyber Resilience Act - Cyber Resilience Act】【3:5†Cyber Resilience Act - Text - SPAC Alliance】【3:4†EU Cyber Resilience Act: Annexes, Guidelines \u0026 Compliance Resources】.\n\n**Practical Implications:**\n- Manufacturers must assemble and maintain this technical documentation to be made available to the relevant national authorities upon request.\n- For critical and important digital products (as defined in the regulation's earlier annexes), the documentation requirements may be more extensive, particularly regarding security assurance.\n\n**Full Text and Annexes:**\nYou can access the entire Regulation (EU) 2024/2847, including its annexes such as Annex VII, via the official EUR-Lex portal for the authentic legal text【3:0†Regulation - 2024/2847 - EN - EUR-Lex】 or browse specific resources dedicated to CRA compliance and guidance【3:1†Read the Latest Commission Guidance on EU CRA Regulation】【3:9†Commission Guidance of REGULATION (EU) 2024/2847 - Cyber Resilience Act】. \n\nIn summary, Annex VII provides a checklist for the structure and content of the technical documentation required for any digital product’s lifecycle within the scope of the Cyber Resilience Act, to support transparency, accountability, and consistent cybersecurity standards throughout the EU.",
